{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Toffee Sauce","content":["Place butter, dark brown sugar and cream in mixing bowl then cook <b>8 min\/120°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a heat-proof jug and set aside to cool completely. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make sponge."]},{"title":"Sponge","content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Grease and line base of 2 loose-based cake tins (Ø 20 cm) with baking paper.","Place margarine and light brown sugar in mixing bowl then cream <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then cream again <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Without measuring cup, set to <b>speed 3<b> then add eggs, one at a time, through hole in mixing bowl lid, stopping once fully incorporated.","Add flour, baking powder and vanilla extract then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Finish mixing by hand with spatula if necessary then divide evenly between prepared tins. Bake for 25-30 minutes (170°C) until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Leave to cool in tins for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make icing."]},{"title":"Buttercream Icing","content":["Place butter, icing sugar and 120 g cooled toffee sauce in mixing bowl then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Bring remaining toffee sauce to a rapid boil in a saucepan on hob then boil for 2 minutes until thickened to a drizzling consistency. Transfer to a heat-proof jug and leave to cool completely."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Cut each cooled sponge in half horizontally with a serrated knife. Layer sponges with buttercream then ice top and sides.","Once thickened toffee sauce has cooled, spread over top and drizzle down the sides. Serve in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Toffee Sauce","content":["80 g unsalted butter, diced","120 g dark brown sugar","200 g double cream"]},{"title":"Sponge","content":["200 g margarine, plus extra for greasing","200 g light brown muscovado sugar","4 large eggs","200 g self-raising flour","1 tsp baking powder","1 tsp vanilla extract"]},{"title":"Buttercream Icing","content":["220 g unsalted butter, diced","350 g icing sugar"]}],"id":"r315425","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-MPW9wIrhk3E\/XZWqXY4FVqI\/AAAAAAAAfWw\/JI8LKOnUA04Y9kgqO3yMh3T3tQWcj8bJQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_JgERiMrUkabYUyCq.png","title":"Sticky Toffee Sponge Cake","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.8 g","fat":"39.9 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"68.3 g","calories":"2748 kJ \/ 658 kcal"},"usefulItems":"skewer, wire rack, saucepan, baking paper, serrated knife, heat-proof jug, loose-based cake tins (Ø 20 cm), oven, hob","hintsAndTricks":["With all the flavours of a classic sticky toffee pudding, this light and golden sponge stands tall and proud. Drizzled with the thickest, stickiest toffee sauce, this is a true showstopper of a cake that is sure to become a family favourite.","Any leftover sauce can be enjoyed drizzled over ice cream or yoghurt."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 30m","12 slices"]}